###################################################
Read me - Food Security
08/31/2015
###################################################
Important notes: 

1.	The subset of households for the SAGCOT area from the Tanzania LSMS 2013 
      data has been selected based on the main regions falling within the 
	  SAGCOT boundaries. We are currently working on improving the selection 
	  process by selecting only households that have enumeration areas falling 
	  within the SAGCOT boundaries. 

###################################################
  1. Tanzania: LSMS 2013 at the SAGCOT level
###################################################

The Food security indicators are generated for the SAGCOT area using the LSMS 2013 data (wave 3), 
   and the following reference data:
   
   CroptozaocodeconversionTZLSMS2013 - crop code conversion to standard food item codes
   TZLSMS_Nutrientlookuptables_2015_08_06 - the list of food items from the survey and their respective
	 nutrient components 
   ​FoodSecurity_ExternalDataTables.xlsx​ - the set of external data tables, including:
	 DRI - the daily recommended nutrient intake for individuals
	 livestock - the livestock conversion to available food consumption (weight per animal)
 
FoodSecurity.TZA.R: script that takes the TZA LSMS 2013 data and reference data as input, 
   and calculates the set of poverty indicators as a csv file 
   with the main indicators from the thread:
•	
•	FS 19 food access score
•	FS 22 food utilization

###################################################
  2. Vital Signs at landscape level (Tier 4)
###################################################


The Food security indicators are generated for the SAGCOT area using the VS household and agriculture data, 
   and the following reference data:
   
   CroptozaocodeconversionTZLSMS2013 - crop code conversion to standard food item codes
   TZLSMS_Nutrientlookuptables_2015_08_06 - the list of food items from the survey and their respective
	 nutrient components 
   ​FoodSecurity_ExternalDataTables.xlsx​ - the set of external data tables, including:
	 DRI - the daily recommended nutrient intake for individuals
	 livestock - the livestock conversion to available food consumption (weight per animal)
 
FoodSecurity.VS.R: script that takes the VS household and agriculture data and reference data as input, 
   and calculates the set of poverty indicators as a csv file 
   with the main indicators from the thread:
•	
•	FS 19 food access score
•	FS 22 food utilization

FoodSecurity.VS.R references a set of functions from the following R files:
VS.R - contains a set of common data staging functions for use with the VS household 
   and agriculture surveys   

